quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  43,1,"Ha, Meem"
  43,2,By the Book that makes things clear
  43,3,"We made it an Arabic Quran, so that you may understand"
  43,4,"And it is with Us, in the Source Book, sublime and wise"
  43,5,"Shall We hold back the Reminder from you, since you are a transgressing people"
  43,6,How many a prophet did We send to the ancients
  43,7,"No messenger came to them, but they ridiculed him"
  43,8,"We destroyed people more powerful than they, and so the example of the ancients has passed away"
  43,9,"And if you asked them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth?' They would say, 'The Mighty, the Knower created them"
  43,10,"He who made the earth a habitat for you, and traced pathways for you on it, that you may be guided"
  43,11,He who sends down water from the sky in due proportion; and so We revive thereby a dead land. Thus you will be brought out
  43,12,"He Who created all the pairs; and provided you with ships, and animals on which you ride"
  43,13,"That you may mount their backs, and remember the favor of your Lord as you sit firmly upon them, and say, 'Glory be to Him Who placed these at our service; surely we could not have done it by ourselves"
  43,14,"And surely, to our Lord we will return"
  43,15,Yet they turn one of His servants into a part of Him. Man is clearly ungrateful